communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all records of communications or meetings since January 1, 2021 between employees of Hadsell, Stormer Renick & Dai LLP and any members of the Los Angeles City Council or their staffs. I am also seeking any and all records of communications or meetings since January 1, 2021 between Sara Flock and any members of the Los Angeles City Council or their staffs. 

These records may include, but are not limited to, any emails sent or received by members of the Los Angeles City Council or their staffs from individuals with an @hadsellstormer.com email address; any logs of phone calls between any members of the Los Angeles City Council or their staffs and 626-775-7870; or any documentation received by members of the Los Angeles City Council or their staffs from 250 E 1st Street, Ste #1201 Los Angeles, CA 90012, or 128 N Fair Oaks Avenue Suite #204 Pasadena, CA 91103.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Stephen Johnson

title: Police 9-1-1 records for 915 W Frier Dr, Phoenix (Phoenix Police Department)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Arizona Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of the list of 9-1-1 and/or non-emergency incident call logs between January 1, 2020, and the date of fulfillment, for 915 W Frier Dr, Phoenix, AZ 85021.

All incident reports from and relating to 915 W Frier Dr, Phoenix, AZ 85021 between January 1, 2020, and the date of fulfillment.

I request that you release records for this request on a rolling basis as they become available and in electronic form.

If your agency does not maintain these public records, please let me know who does and include the proper custodian's name and address.

If you choose to deny this request, please provide a written explanation for the denial including a reference to the specific statutory exemption(s) upon which you rely. Also, please provide all segregable portions of otherwise exempt material.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Albert Serna Jr.
